  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Breakfast School Feeding Programme is implemented by the NGO called Feed the Children Tanzania. Main objectives of the activities are as follows:  1) to alleviate short-term hunger in malnourished or otherwise well nourished school children. This helps to increase the attention and concentration of students producing gains in cognitive function and learning 2) to motivate parents to enroll their children in school and have them attend regularly 3) to address specific micronutrient deficiencies in schoolage children 4) to increase community involvement in schools particularly where programs depend on the community to prepare and serve meals to children.
Thus , the project will conduct introductory school feeding awareness creation training; construct simple kitchens; construct energy efficient wood burning stoves; purchase cooking pots and initial supply of food.</narrative>
  </description>
